Personal lockers;
Network printing;
Boardrooms;
Lounge;
Fully equipped kitchenette with free coffee;
Daily cleaning;
Shower facilities;
Two relaxing patios.
Access to La Gratitude’s Italian restaurant. Atterbury said that the co-working space also has a number of security features including biometrics and a security application which enables 24/7 access for working any time of the day or night. <img class="size-full wp-image-348142 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-8.jpg" alt="" width="1536" height="1025" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-8.jpg 1536w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-8-300x200.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-8-768x513.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-8-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-8-1200x801.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-348144 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-10.jpg" alt="" width="1025" height="1536" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-10.jpg 1025w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-10-200x300.jpg 200w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-10-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Atta-10-683x1024.jpg 683w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> “The Attspace 15-seater open-plan shared workspace is a prestigious business address suited to a diverse variety of users, from entrepreneurs and start-ups to freelancers and small business owners,” the group said. “Personalised packages are available to users’ requirements to get them started right away.” Read: This South African property group is dropping ‘elite’ developments – because the economy can’t take it 